annotationA: 40S ribosomal protein S2; Has a specific developmental role during oogenesis and a general role in protein synthesis as a component of the small ribosomal subunit
annotationB: Eukaryotic initiation factor 1A, isoform A; Seems to be required for maximal rate of protein biosynthesis. Enhances ribosome dissociation into subunits and stabilizes the binding of the initiator Met-tRNA(I) to 40 S ribosomal subunits
